The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) in Niger Sate has said that one person died while four were seriously injured in an accident, which occurred along Minna-Bida road in Bosso Local Government Area, NAN reports. The FRSC Sector Commander, Mr. Joel Dagwa, told journalists in Minna on Saturday that the unfortunate incident, which happened at about 4:45 a.m., involved two vehicles with registration numbers MNA 488 VC and RBC 579 YB and a motorcycle without a registration number. Dagwa explained that five people were involved in the accident, which resulted in the death of one person. According to him, the two vehicles and one motorcycle have been cleared from the road and handed over to Kpakungu police division. He said that the victims were taken to General Hospital Minna, where a doctor confirmed the female victim dead and the rider was referred to IBB Specialist Hospital. He also blamed the accident on wrong overtaking and speed violation while advising that motorists should exercise caution and adhere strictly to speed limits, to avoid unnecessary loss of lives and property. “We will continue to sustain our aggressive patrols in and outside the metropolis to ensure that road users adhere strictly to traffic rules and regulations to avoid road accidents,” he added. Auto crash kills three in Niger Two dead, four injured in Ogun road crash 1 die, 4 injured in multiple accidents on Abeokuta-Lagos expressway